{"questionId":"9901","questionHtml":"<p>Verify that&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = 800\"> <mi>x</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mn>800</mn> </math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = 600\"> <mi>y</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mn>600</mn> </math></span>&nbsp;is an equilibrium point.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>substitute&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = 800\"> <mi>x</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mn>800</mn> </math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = 600\"> <mi>y</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mn>600</mn> </math></span>&nbsp;into both equations&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p>both equations equal 0&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>hence an equilibrium point &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9901","referenceCode":"SPM.3.AHL.TZ0.2b.i","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Verify that x = 800 , y = 600 is an equilibrium point.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"b.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.16—Eulers method for 1st order DEs"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}